items.name: Milk Bath
items.description:
Join our Discord to see more images and upcoming updates!

Introduction

Milk Bath is a LoRA which was trained on mostly nude woman lying in milk water. Cleopatra also added honey so the trigger word contains honey too.

Training Resolution: 512x768 (2:3) + 768x512 (3:2)

Trained on Real Hot Mix but also works on other models.

How to Use

Strenght 0.4-0.8

Lower the value if you want to reduce nudes or if you want to show other objects.

CFG 5-7

Prompts

woman lying in milkandhoney (for nudes)

(something lying in milkandhoney:1.2) to show something (add woman to negative)

If you just want milkandhoney without the bath tub, add bath tub to negative (works not in all cases).

front view, rear view, side view if you depict a woman

Some objects just float on the water and just don't work even if you add strenght. Objects that are usually in water work better. See promo images for more examples and see the LoRA metadata for a full tag list on how to control nudes.

items.name: Female on Top from Side
items.description:
The goal of this model was to create more coherent sex scenes with the female characters on top of the male character, with a focus on showing both characters and viewing from the side. This LoRA does usually get the scene, however, be warned that issues will appear often and will need inpainting to fix, such as funky hands or extra limbs, which will need to be inpainted out. However, due to the increased reliability, it is helpful to have this to help push the model in the right direction.

The trigger word is side cowgirl. Using from side and hetero can help depending on the model. Adding penis will often add one, but expect a higher percentage of errors. The model did include some female and female and male on male content so it does help with these scenes as well with some further prompting. Generally, I use a higher weight and play with 0.7-1 depending on the model and what I am trying to achieve.

The first two images are examples of pure text to img generations, while the others have been touched up with img2img to fix them up.

items.name: Desi Coffee LoCon
items.description:
This is an experimental Lycoris/LoCon to produce 3 Indian skin tones ranging from Light (Latte), to Medium (Mocha), to Dark (Espresso).

Please note that this tends to produce NSFW images. Also LoCons are quirky, and this particular one's quirk is that it needs the trigger word and the <lyco> tag to be next to each other.

Compared to the LoRA, (https://civitai.com/models/83442/desi-coffee), this is about 1/5th the size, but took about 3.5 hours to train, on the same data set.

Does tend to produce darker skin-tones than the LoRA, so that's something I'm working on an may follow up with a separate version on.

Suggested settings:

  1. CFG: 6-7.5

  2. Steps: 20-30

  3. Sampler: euler a followed by DDIM in img2img for upscaling

  4. Strength: 0.7-1

  5. Clipskip: 1 or 2. 2 tends to work better with some models.

Comments and suggestions welcome.

items.name: CinematicStyleV1
items.description:
Introducing CinematicStyleV1 LoRA, a powerful LoRA that captures moments in a visually striking and storytelling manner, reminiscent of scenes from movies. This LoRA is designed to create a sense of drama, depth, and emotion in your AI-generated images. With its unique capabilities, your images will be bathed in warm, golden light, casting long shadows and creating a captivating atmosphere that transports viewers into a cinematic world.

Immerse yourself in the art of visual storytelling as you harness the transformative power of CinematicStyleV1 LoRA. Whether you're creating portraits, landscapes, or any other type of imagery, this style will elevate your creations to new heights, evoking emotions and narratives with every pixel.

Make sure you add keyword  111cine8matic55 to your prompt to trigger the style.

Start with a lower weight and work your way up as each weight adds a different degree of style. 0.5 and 1 work well but you may find a lower or higher value works best depending on your prompt.

<lora:CineStyle5:0.5> 111cine8matic55 

My example images have no other LoRA's, or textual inversions and only have a Default_Negative prompt so you can really see what the model can do without anything else effecting the results.

For those seeking inspiration in generating text-to-image prompts, our accompanying ChatGPT primer prompt is an invaluable resource. It has been carefully crafted to complement and optimize the visual output of all my LoRA's. Access the primer prompt here:  HERE

By exploring the below grids, you'll gain invaluable insights into how various weights influence the image

The below weights: No lora, 0.5, 0.7, 1

Michael Corbett Shannon (born August 7, 1974)[1] is an American actor. items.description:
A commission of @Zorglub.

Lauren Graham is an American actress, mainly known for her role as Lorelai Gilmore on the TV show Gilmore Girls.

130-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (l4ur3ngrah4m:0.99), a woman as a movie star, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

items.name: Virile Animation
items.description:
If you'd like to buy me a beer or coffee! 🍺☕

⚠️ Make sure to read the below Clip Skip instructions ⚠️

This model is my fourth merge and has been fine-tuned in order to produce convincing male-focused gens without the need for Loras, even with simple prompts.

This model attempts to explore a more "drawn/anime" look.

It is built upon my three previous merges, Virile Fusion, Virile Reality and Virile Motion, however it is not a replacement and only aims at offering a different style, which could not be achieved by my three other models.

In the end, whichever model you decide to use is a matter of preference.

⚠️ I highly recommend using this model with Clip Skip set to 1 for better results ⚠️

NB: Clip skip 2 works fine and might even give you less artifacts, but the style will be less "flat" - At the end of the day, it is a matter of preference.

The best way to change your Clip Skip on the fly is to open A1111, go to Settings > User Interface. In there, if you scroll a bit, you will find a "Quicksettings" option:

Add the following option by typing the first letters and then picking from the drop-down list: CLIP_stop_at_last_layers

Apply Settings and Reload UI at the top of the page.

If done correctly, you should now be able to change your Clip Skip on the fly via an option now present on the left of your screen:

Models included in the merge are:

  • Virile Fusion

  • ToonYou

  • MatureMaleMix

  • Mistoon Amethyst

Loras included in the merge are:

  • The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild Style LoRA

  • Tgirls

  • Detail Tweaker LoRA

While the model has been crafted to be male-centric, it also allows for the generation of other types of characters (including females) as well as landscapes, or objects.

Recommended settings for gens that look like the samples (Automatic1111):

Config 1:

  • Clip Skip: 1 (see above for instructions)

  • Sampling Method: Euler A

  • Sampling Steps: 60

  • Hires. fix On

  • Upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B

  • Hires Steps: 30

  • Denoising Strength: 0.4

  • Upscale: 1.5/2.0

  • Width: 512

  • Height: 768

  • CFG Scale: 5

Example:

Config 2:

  • Clip Skip: 1 (see above for instructions)

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Sampling Steps: 30

  • Hires. fix On

  • Upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B

  • Hires Steps: 15

  • Denoising Strength: 0.4

  • Upscale: 1.5/2.0

  • Width: 512

  • Height: 768

  • CFG Scale: 5

Example:

Both configs are valid, they really are a matter of preference. I personally prefer the cleanliness of Euler A, but some will prefer what DPM offers. Try both and take your pick!

I also highly recommend using After Detailer for faces, using the "face_yolov8n.pt" model. This will change your life.

Extension and instructions can be found here.

VAE-wise, I would advise to use the following one: kl-f8-anime2 VAE.

It'll make your gens a lot more colorful and enjoyable, at least in my opinion.

I would also like to mention and thank the Unstable Diffusion Discord Server's #men-only community who helped me learn a lot. Some of the gens done with the model include their prompts.

Also, to those people who left thumbs down on all the previous pictures that contained male nudity, thanks for the reactions! It actually makes the pictures more popular! No such thing as bad publicity. Also, this is a space for everyone, whether you like it or not.

items.name: BeautyFool
items.description:
This model was created by mixing several different models with each other after patient and hard trials. It is the perfect choice for creating realistic looking anime pictures. You can also create more linear images by entering the correct prompts.

As a sampling method, Euler A provides excellent results.

CFG Scale must be at least 7 and Sampling steps must be at least 20.

I recommend using "4x-AnimeSharp" or "R-ESRGAN 4X+ Anime6B" as upscaler.

I usually use Clip Skip as 2 but 1 also gives good results

"Bad-hands-5", "bad_pictures" and "EasyNegative" are great for negative embedding.

I generally prefer to use hires fix instead of using restore faces. Restored faces often damage the expressions on the faces and the originality of the eyes.

I recommend adding negative embeddings and using hires fix to get decent results. Let your Hires fix steps be at least half of your sampling steps. Believe me, it will be worth it.

I can't do model training yet. For now, I'm just merging. I download gigabytes of files from civitai every day and now I have 5TB of data :) on the other hand, I'm trying to learn. I am trying to get proper results by mixing the appropriate loras and checkpoints with each other in certain proportions and I share the results that I find successful with you. Sometimes I don't remember what materials were included in the final model because I mixed too much. I guess I'll have to keep a long list to get around the problem. Very soon I will start to share the loras that I have produced myself. Sorry for my english because i don't know english :)

My work will continue...

After this work, a coffee wouldn't be bad at all.

items.name: MaiMix
items.description:
Check out my other sibling model for semi-realistic anime style art: MaiMixSR

MaiMix is an anime illustration style model which aims to produce high quality art with little prompting at low steps but even greater results with more complex prompts.

All sample images have been generated without the use of textual inversion/negative embeddings and VAE at 512x768 resolution (no upscaling) with no extra features to display the strength of the model. For real world use it is recommended that ClearVAE and EasyNegative is used for even higher quality results. Hires.fix and/or Adetailer is recommended for images where the character is more distant for better results.

MaiMixHard is an updated version based on a line art illustration style.

MaiMixSoft is an updated version based on a brush stroke illustration style.

MaiMixBeta is the original generalist MaiMix with an illustration style closer to the base model used.

NSFW is supported but NSFW LoRA's may be needed for better results.

Recommended Settings (VAE Not Baked):

Sampler: Euler or DPM++ 2M Karras (25-50 steps)
CFG Scale: 4 to 11 (7.5 preferred for balanced outputs)
Clip Skip: 2 for more variation but model works well with 1 as well.
Negatives (if not using EasyNegative): ((low quality!!, worst quality!!, monochrome noir)), AND bad anatomy, AND hideous extra bad hands, AND auxiliary missing malformed fingers, AND unrefined duplicate body parts, AND fused overlap unseparated conjoined, AND (strabismus, (red eyes)), AND fused merged additional arms, AND baby face, AND child, AND loli, AND childlike, AND young, AND (((corner text!, watermark!, logo!, signature!, words!, letters!, content!, artist name!, trademark!, inscription!, symbol!, hieroglyph!, glyphs!, type!, scribble!))), face tattoos, face paint, scars, misplaced multiple boobs, inaccurate nipples, Asian face, transsexual, hermaphrodite, deformed malformed, twisted, mutilated, blur, haze, censor

Model Design Aim:

MaiMix is designed as a proof-of-concept weight merge model using LoRA's only to further train and fine-tune models to produce new model characteristics and improvements over base models. items.name: 家でやろう。Let's do it at home
items.description:
Let's do it at home is a successful ad campaign for good manners on the Tokyo metro

https://www.spoon-tamago.com/please-do-it-tokyo-metro-manner-posters-by-bunpei-yorifuji/

The model is not very good (few training samples)

Included Loras:

  • iede: normal

  • iede_tsurainichijou: the model was confused by all the angry faces and started painting bleak black and white pictures

  • iede_ukiyoe: the model though that this was half illustration/half ukiyoe (or 'old Japanese manga' without the activation word)

prompt:

iede, <<scene description>>, metro, halftone, simple_background, white_background, yellow_theme <lora:iede:1>

Additional notes:

  • the font for english text seems to be something close to Helvetica, Helvetica Pro or Swiss 721

  • the font for japanese seems to be close to Genjuu Gothic P Heavy

  • more manners: watch?v=FUyNLTHcgbI

Bad日本語版

「家でやろう。」のポスターのLoraです

Lora三つあります：

  • 普通、学習例えが少ない為、別によくない

  • 辛い日常：学習途中で、モデルが皆の辛い顔に合わせたくて、喜びのない黒白世界を描きました

  • 浮世絵：学習途中で、モデルがイラストと浮世絵の絵に混乱して、スタイルを混ぜました （activation wordを含まないと、五十年前のイラストも出ます）

プロンプト

iede, <<scene description>>, metro, halftone, simple_background, white_background, yellow_theme <lora:iede:1>

フォントはよく解りませんが、ロマジはHelvetica系かな、日本語は源柔ゴシックPHeavyかな。

マナ－：watch?v=FUyNLTHcgbI

items.name: Number Six (The Prisoner)
items.description:
Number Six is the central character in the 1967–1968 television series The Prisoner. The unnamed character in the original TV series was played by series co-creator Patrick McGoohan.

After abruptly and angrily resigning from his high-ranking government job, Number Six prepares to make a hurried departure from the country. The most he will later reveal about his resignation is that it was a "matter of conscience".

While packing his luggage, he is rendered unconscious by knockout gas piped into his London home. When he wakes, he finds himself in a re-creation of the interior of his home, located in a mysterious coastal "village" within which he is held captive, isolated from the mainland by mountains and sea.

The series is currently available on DVD, BluRay and legally for free on YouTube.
